          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Here’s a practical “match-by-use-case” guide:</p><ul><li><strong>Best all-around folding, high comfort, and strong brakes</strong>:<br/><strong>Hunter Pro</strong> – Features <strong>full suspension</strong>, <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, <strong>95 Nm</strong> of torque, <strong>48V 15Ah</strong> battery, up to <strong>80 miles</strong> range, and <strong>400 lb</strong> payload. Perfect for long rides across varying terrain.</li><li><strong>Best value folding fat tire for mixed terrain</strong>:<br/><strong>X-Hunter</strong> – A <strong>folding model</strong>, with <strong>85 Nm</strong> of torque, <strong>48V 13Ah</strong> battery, and up to <strong>70 miles</strong> range. Great for riders seeking an affordable but versatile fat tire eBike.</li><li><strong>Best step-through accessibility and hydraulic brakes</strong>:<br/><strong>X-Hunter ST</strong> – A <strong>low-step frame</strong> model with <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, <strong>up to 71 miles</strong> range, and <strong>480 lb</strong> payload capacity. Ideal for easy mounting and urban commuting.</li><li><strong>Best 26\" platform for taller riders and long-range battery</strong>:<br/><strong>Thunder Pro</strong> – With <strong>26\" x 4\" tires</strong>, a <strong>52V 20Ah</strong> battery, <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, and up to <strong>90 miles</strong> of range, this is the go-to for riders looking for stability at higher speeds and rougher roads.</li><li><strong>Fastest moped-style eBike with 52V system</strong>:<br/><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong> – Featuring <strong>full suspension</strong>, <strong>52V 20Ah</strong> battery, up to <strong>90 miles</strong> range, and speeds up to <strong>38 mph</strong> with pedal assist, this is ideal for those seeking maximum speed and comfort.</li></ul>"
